#!CDarkGreen #!N  #!Rcamset Precise Camera Settings #!N #!EC #!N 
#!N In addition to using direct interactors to change camera settings, 
Data Explorer lets you specify exact values to the camera for 
more precise results. You can also use this feature to learn 
the exact camera settings that result from your use of direct 
interactors. These settings correspond to parameters of the Camera module. (See 
 #!Lcamera,dxall780 h Camera  #!EL  in IBM Visualization Data Explorer User's Reference.) #!N #!N To 
access the camera settings, select the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Camera #!EF mode using 
the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Mode #!EF option box in the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   View Control... 
#!EF dialog box or the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Ctrl+K #!EF accelerator key. The 
camera controls appear on the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   View Control... #!EF dialog box, 
as illustrated in  #!Lcamset58,dxall310 f Figure 58  #!EL  . #!Cbrown #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*    #!Rcamset58 #!N Graphics 
omitted from Online Documentation. Please see the manual. #!N #!N Figure 
58. Camera Settings Portion of the View Control Dialog Box #!EF 
#!N #!EC #!N #!N Note that these camera controls are not 
direct interactors, so changing their values does not cause the visual 
program to reexecute automatically. To see the effect of your changes, 
you must specify  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Execute #!EF or  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Execute on Change 
#!EF in the VPE, Control Panel, or Image window. #!N #!N 
